{
  "id" : 763,
  "songNumber" : 151,
  "title" : "TEMPTED AND TRIED WE'RE OFT MADE TO WONDER",
  "language" : "english",
  "originalKey" : "D",
  "capo" : 0,
  "bpm" : 0,
  "timeSignature" : "4/4",
  "hashtags" : [ ],
  "sections" : [ {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "VERSE 1",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "Tempted and tried we're oft made to wonder",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Why it should be thus all the day long,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 17
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 34
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "While there are others living about us,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 16
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Never molested though in the wrong.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 29
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "Farther along we'll know all about it,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Farther along we'll understand why;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 25
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Cheer up, my brother, live in the sunshine,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "We'll understand it all by and by.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 11
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 31
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "When death has come and taken our loved ones,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "It leaves our home so lonely and drear,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 22
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 33
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then do we wonder why others prosper,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 11
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Living so wicked year after year.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 28
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "Faithful till death said our loving Master,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "A few more days to labor and wait;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 19
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 29
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Toils of the road will then seem as nothing,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "As we sweep through the beautiful gate.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 24
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "When we see Jesus coming in glory,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 8
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "When He comes from His home in the sky;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 23
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 35
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then we shall meet Him in that bright mansion,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 14
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "We'll understand it all by and by."
    } ]
  } ]
}